Asm-Z80-Table

This module provides hash tables to assemble / disassemble all Z80 CPU assembly instructions, including undocumented ones (e.g. 'ld ixh,N') and instructions composed by sequences (e.g. 'ld bc,hl').

This module is used in a Z80 assembler / disassembler.

It was spun off the CPU::Z80::Assembler module.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Asm::Z80::Table

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Asm-Z80-Table

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Asm-Z80-Table

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Asm-Z80-Table

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Asm-Z80-Table/


